Convert original RGB image to grayscale image

In [35]:
def rgb2gray(rgb_image):
    image_8bit = np.round(np.sum(rgb_image * np.array([0.114, 0.587, 0.299]), axis=-1)).astype('uint8')
    image_8bit[0,0]=255 #to compensate for the loss of 1 gray value during conversion
    plt.figure(figsize=(12,12))
    plt.imshow(image_8bit , cmap='gray')
    plt.title('8 bit grayscale image')
    return image_8bit

gray_image = rgb2gray(image)

2 Equalize histogram¶

In [38]:
#compute the probability of an occurrence of a pixel of level i in the image
#where n_total is the total number of pixels in the image
n_total = gray_image.ravel().shape[0]
prob_i = bin_counts / n_total
plt.plot(prob_i)
plt.title('probability distribution')
plt.show()


#compute cumulative sum ==  accumulated normalized histogram of the image
cumulative_sum = np.array([sum(prob_i[:i+1]) for i in range(len(bin_counts))])

plt.plot(cumulative_sum)
plt.title('cumulative sum ==  accumulated normalized histogram')
plt.show()

#get equalized histogram by renormalizing the cumulative sum
hist_equalized =  (cumulative_sum - cumulative_sum.min()) * 255  / (cumulative_sum.max() - cumulative_sum.min())
plt.plot(hist_equalized)
plt.title('equalized cumulative sum')
plt.show()

# get the values of the equalized histogram for the corresponding values of the flatten original image
gray_image_equalized = hist_equalized[gray_image.ravel()]
plt.hist(gray_image_equalized, bins=256)
plt.title('equalized histogram')
